tervail247365]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>How We Blocked a Coal Plant and Got a Solar Plant, Instead</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XiummPU</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/86FQpBn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I don't know who needs to hear this, but: 

A few years ago, I moved my family to a rural valley in the Western US. Beautiful. I found out a few weeks later that there were plans for a company from Las Vegas to build an enormous coal-fired power plant here, with 400-foot tall smokestacks, and all the massive pollution that'd come with it.

I get the need for electricity, but it was a poor choice of location. I asked the Vegas ppl, off the record, why here? They said the rest of the state already violated clean air laws. Experts predicted a loss of 6-12 years of life for every resident if it was built. 
So, I started a website, email newsletter, got local cable TV access for broadcasting public hearings, and set up a magazine to get the word out that not everyone was okay with that. 

Others agreed. One local lady set up a voting initiative that power plants would need voters' approval. And because the group had no money to speak of, a couple of non-lawyer friends put a court challenge together. 

The case went to the state supreme court. We won. It turned out that the only evidence of research for the permit to pollute our valley was a scribbled approval on a post-it note. 

Some locals complained the local government had lost out on tax revenues. But a few months later, a solar power station was proposed by another company. That's part of it, in the photo. It's silent, clean, peaceful -- and everyone is living 6-12 years longer. 

Not all superheroes wear capes. Don't let people, including wealthy people, push you around.

Save your worlds, my dudes, and you help save the whole world. 

(Below is what that area would have looked like, had the coal-fired power plant been built.)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wOPcpEx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XiummPU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MeanwhileInAmerica]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Too soon?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TizriAx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cpPdH0D.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TizriAx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ChemistryAndPhysicsAreFun]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This is Zoe Thorogood, she's an author and artist</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/kwWFfJK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pfrVHl0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I've been following her for a while and love her stuff.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sR5vByc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here is some of the stuff she has worked on IT’S LONELY AT THE CENTRE OF THE EARTH - JOE HILL’S RAIN - LIFE IS STRANGE - HACK/SLASH - HARLEY QUINN - CREEPSHOW</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PMkMkWw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mNhvGZ8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>She along with several other artists recently had a problem with the art company that was repping them. See what's currently known of the story here, https://www.comicsbeat.com/what-is-happening-at-cadence-comic-art/ . Likely more details will come out over time.

