The city I live in has 3 ballot measures coming next month, and one of them would allow the city to demand voter identification (a tactic commonly used to disenfranchise minorities) and allow the city to post "monitors" at polling places and ballot drop-off boxes. 

Yes, these would obviously be overturned in court as unconstitutional, but it means that for the Nov 2024 election they would have an opportunity to have these weekend warriors with their weapons on display demanding voters show ID before allowing them to drop off a ballot or go into a voting booth.

Do not skip the primaries, this is where the GOP is laying groundwork to challenge the November election.

